How to re-enable the login features:

STEP 1: go to https://console.developers.google.com and start a new project.

STEP 2: navigate to APIs under APIs & auth. Enable the Google+ API.

STEP 3: navigate to chrome://extensions. Select developer mode and load the project folder as an unpacked extension. Copy the ID that chrome assigns to the extension.

STEP 4: navigate back to the project in the Google developer console and go to credentials under APIs & auth.

STEP 5: Click Add Credential and select OAuth2.0 client ID.

STEP 6: Configure the consent screen.

Step 7: Select Chrome App and enter the extension ID into the Application ID field.

Step 8: Copy the provided Client ID into the Client_Id field in manifest.JSON.